                  Felix Pfaefflis Pop Infused Graphic Posters | Beautiful/Decay Artist &amp; Design
                 </h4>
                 <div class="fadeContainer">
                  <div class="hoverMask">
                  </div>
                  <div class="Image Module pinUiImage" id="Image-200" style="width: 236px">
                   <div class="heightContainer" style="padding-bottom: 140.254237%">
                    <img alt="Designer: Felix Pfffli - http://www.feixen.ch" class="pinImg fullBleed" onload="P.lazy.onImageLoad(this)" src="https://s-media-cache-ak0.pinimg.com/236x/ad/52/b1/ad52b1d0638a93a5e7886f2adc061a98.jpg" style=""/>

              <div class="pinMeta ">
               <p class="pinDescription">
                Designer: Felix Pfffli -
                <a href="http://www.feixen.ch" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">
                 www.feixen.ch

               <h4 class="vaseText hidden">
                Design Inspiration, Screens Prints, Picture-Black Posters, Graphicdesign, Digital Art, Posters Design, Typographic Posters, Graphics Design, Swiss Design
               </h4>
               <h4 class="vaseText hidden">
                swiss design
               </h4>
               <h4 class="vaseText hidden">
                Felix Pfaeffli via #grainedit Im very impressed with these posters from Felix Pfaeffli, an accomplished young designer from Luzern who is producing very polished and mature work for his age. In addition to running his own studio he is a teacher at the Lucerne School of Graphic Design where he lectures on typography, narrative design, and poster design.
               </h4>
               <h4 class="vaseText hidden">
                graphic design inspirations
               </h4>
               <h4 class="vaseText hidden">
                Suedpol is a multi purpose cultural center in Kriens, Switzerland, close to Lucerne, that houses a theater, a symphony orchestra, a brass band, a music school, a restaurant, a flea market, and rents its rooms for performances of music, dance, theatre, literature, digital arts and so on. All posters are printed in size 42 x 30 cm using the Risograph technique, a kind of small scale silk screen printing.
               </h4>
               <h4 class="vaseText hidden">
                Typographic poster design
               </h4>
